# Cyclic Patterns Test Corpus (X → Y → X)
# Reference: docs/theory/cyclic-pattern-analysis.md
# Purpose: Validate cyclic pattern recognition and semantic coherence

# ============================================================================
# Core Pattern Structure
# ============================================================================
# X → Y → X where:
# - X1 = initial state
# - Y = complement/contrast/other
# - X2 = X1 + experience(Y) = transformed X
#
# Key insight: X2 is not identical to X1 despite same word.
# The return incorporates the experience of Y.

# ============================================================================
# High-Resonance Patterns (Universal emotional appeal)
# ============================================================================

# Journey Pattern: yo → an → yo
yo → an → yo
# home → away → home (the traveler's return)
# Initial: familiarity
# Transition: foreign experience
# Return: home knowing "away"

# Empathy Pattern: sel → oth → sel
sel → oth → sel
# self → other → self (hero's journey)
# Initial: individual isolation
# Transition: understanding other
# Return: self containing other

# Learning Pattern: kno → nu kno → kno
kno → nu kno → kno
# knowing → not-knowing → knowing (Socratic method)
# Initial: confident knowledge
# Transition: confusion/humility
# Return: deeper knowledge

