# ============================================================================
# Pattern Detection Test
# ============================================================================
# Computational verification:

whe pat_start
whe pat_mid
whe pat_end

pat_start sa pat_end
pat_mid sa nu pat_start

# If pat_start = pat_end AND pat_mid = nu pat_start
# Then valid X → Y → X pattern detected

# ============================================================================
# Expanded Poetic Forms
# ============================================================================

# Three-word minimal:
sel | oth | sel

# With liminal marker:
sel oth bet | tog

# Multi-cycle composition:
kno → nu kno → kno
lov → los → lov
beg → end → beg
alw cyc | nu end

# (knowing → not-knowing → knowing)
# (love → loss → love)
# (beginning → ending → beginning)
# (always cycling | no end)

# ============================================================================
# Validation Rubric
# ============================================================================
# For each pattern:
# 1. Does Y represent nu X or complement of X? (Score: 0-1)
# 2. Is X2 semantically different from X1? (Score: 0-1)
# 3. Does the cycle create emotional resonance? (Score: 0-1)
# 4. Is the pattern recognized cross-culturally? (Score: 0-1)
#
# High-resonance patterns score 3-4/4
# Medium patterns score 2/4
# Low patterns score 0-1/4

